wiki.summary: On “Up Up and Away,“ Juice takes drugs to take him all the way above everyone else. Mentioning the downsides of his fame and wealth, he sings a similar track to much of his debut studio album, Goodbye & Good Riddance, which was released in May 2018. The track was leaked on January 29, 2020, and was eventually posthumously released on Juice WRLD’s third studio album Legends Never Die. “Up Up and Away” debuted at #42 on the Billboard charts during the week of July 25th, 2020. Read more on Last.fm.
